727813f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, north side, just west of 63rd Road, showing an old farmstead. It was owned by Eifert in 1891
and by one Uht in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  June 8, 1927

725548f-a.text:
63rd Road, east from Queens Boulevard. On the left is the H. Vancerveer house of 1860. A. Uhl owned it from 1873 to 1896. The house on the right was owned by the Vanderveers
from 1860 to 1890.
Augene L. Armbruster Collection  April, 1923

727715f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard (left), at the N.W. corner of Junction Boulevard, showing Howard Johnson's Tavern. On the right is
Junction Boulevard, running north.
P. L. Sperr  July 1, 1940
727715f-a.folder: Queens Boulevard & Junction Boulevard, Queens, NY
